        "body": "<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/24535189/composing-multipart-form-data-with-a-different-content-type-on-each-parts-with-j\">Composing multipart/form-data with a different Content-Type on each parts with Javascript (or Angular)<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>I try following the answer in this question and it works. <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>fd.append('whole', new Blob([JSON.stringify({\n        ID: ID,\n        name1:file1.name,\n        name2:file2.name,\n    })], {\n        type: \"application/json\"\n    }));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>The Request class is just as I mentioned.\nThe name1,name2 part is not needed but I just want to test with an Object with various attributes.\nMuch appreciation for Naman's help about FormDataContentDisposition.<\/p>\n",
